column3: Eerie Canal Towpath Run - 15 Mile Race
Week 13: Got lost trying to do MP
column5: missed the turn onto Leland and barreled through trees, puddles, and chest-high grass for 5 miles

3:06:23, 66th place

Rough finish but feeling positive overall. Quads felt some pain around miles 4-6 and starting giving out completely at 18. But everything else felt great, paced myself well at a very comfortable pace, no injuries or cramps. Actually around miles 16-17 I was thinking I went out too conservatively and I should pick it up (famous last words). But I guess that is par for the course for a first marathon. Need to be more aggressive about hydrating since the small cups they were handing out every 2 miles were not enough; lost about 5 pounds in water weight. Good weather for May but still very humid compared to the last few months of training. Lots of room to improve for attempt #2 in the fall.

so I jumped the barriers and ran across I-90...
nice day & windy. some lingering effects from flu but otherwise felt good. fun way to ring in the year

2:56:10, 5th overall

Pretty safe BQ! (I hope)

Beautiful point to point course with wide open sweeping views of the river & islands (and unfortunately 26 straight miles of headwind). Dealt with some cramps on and off most of the race and really had to back off to avoid my calves locking up in the last 5 miles. Need to start taking two full cups of water at every station, even when it's cool and cloudy. Legs felt OK but not great. Looking forward to trying Boston next year!
watch randomly stopped and I didn't notice for a bit

2:49:16, 8th overall and 2nd age group

Disappointingly warm and humid for December, but I felt good and ran a great race. First sub 2:50! Lets go!

17:20 official

Very windy day and mostly ran alone. Was fun to get cheers from Cat & the Hamilton team. I thought I was in better shape, but oh well.

At least this officially breaks my PR of 17:47 set at 13 years old. I am finally faster than I was as a middle schooler!
